The paper deals with an online decision-making problem in which a learner chooses a list of items based on some side information and receives feedback values for each item. This problem is relevant to several domains, including crowdsourcing and recommendation systems, which are covered by the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions real-world learning-to-rank datasets, which further supports the relevance of the paper to these sub-categories.
